HEAT vegetable oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, for 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is tender. Add broth, tomatoes, chiles, lime juice and salt. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes. Add chicken; cook for 3 to 4 minutes. LADLE soup into bowls. Top with chips, avocado and cilantro before serving.